					  FINAL RESULTS: 2010 Ohio Amateur Championship  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  July 16, 2010    1 Comment  

					 

 Michael Bernard of the Dayton suburb of Huber Heights became the youngest champion in the 104-year history of the Ohio Amateur Championship today. The 16-year-old posted a final-round even-par 71 at Kirtland Country Club in Willoughby to finish the 72-hole tournament with a score of 7-under 277, good for a five shot victory.  [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

