 Watch Northeast Ohio Golf for details and an entry blank in the spring… 

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  A Steady Snow as Field Falls in Ohio Senior Am  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  August 19, 2009    No Comments  

					 

 Skip Snow of Dayton played steady golf while the rest of the field backed up, and steady was what it took to win the 2009 Ohio Senior Amateur Championship at Congress Lake on Wednesday. 
 Snow began the day two behind the leaders and posted his second straight 2-over par 73. The 4-over par 146 total was good for for a one shot victory over Ray Sovik and Tom Elfers. Complete results follow: 
